Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:36.03,Ep_Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,520)}Painful Countdown
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.11,0:01:33.82,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.14,0:01:37.24,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,This rod's 37,500 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:42.03,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time, I was trying to buy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.03,0:01:44.79,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,,0000,0000,0000,,something with money I had earned myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.14,0:01:47.21,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The reel's 33,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.21,0:01:48.98,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The cap's 3,500 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:51.13,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's 10,000 yen for the polarized glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.14,0:01:53.80,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,With the rest of your \Nwear and life jacket...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:55.71,handwriting,ENVELOPE,0000,0000,0000,,Salary
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.80,0:01:55.71,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Will I have enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.73,0:02:00.04,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,All together, your total \Ncomes to 102,500 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.81,0:02:05.01,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a discount and \Nmake it an even 100,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:12.77,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.77,0:02:15.54,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Most of my pay's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.54,0:02:19.05,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but now I can finally \Nassemble my own tackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.05,0:02:20.86,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's great, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.86,0:02:21.41,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.41,0:02:23.09,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haru, you're not going to buy anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.09,0:02:23.76,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.74,0:02:25.58,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you should buy something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.59,0:02:27.41,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You got paid to work, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.82,0:02:31.50,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I won't fish any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.28,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.28,0:02:36.89,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Because fishing is lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.89,0:02:38.92,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,And the ocean's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.92,0:02:42.81,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.81,0:02:45.19,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No more fishing! Forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.19,0:02:47.61,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.61,0:02:48.85,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:50.85,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who said we should fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:53.17,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No fishing for you, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.81,0:02:55.89,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.89,0:02:57.62,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No fishing! Forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.30,0:02:59.40,Tsuritama_Italic_Overlap,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a hypocrite now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:02:58.59,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.59,0:02:59.99,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not making any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:00.90,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:00.90,Tsuritama_Overlap,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:05.16,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Yamada, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.83,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was there to witness it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.21,0:03:10.19,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.19,0:03:11.54,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.77,0:03:18.26,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Bermuda Syndrome is the work of aliens,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.59,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and JF1 is one of their kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.45,0:03:24.32,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:26.23,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I saw it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:28.59,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Did you record the event?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.59,0:03:30.68,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it happened so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:33.46,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,We understand your speculation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.46,0:03:35.23,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but we are curious about one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:36.52,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Twinkle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:38.85,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you go fishing with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.85,0:03:41.70,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,To observe JF1, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:43.54,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.07,0:03:45.17,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.17,0:03:48.92,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay an appropriate distance \Nfrom the target at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.92,0:03:50.13,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.13,0:03:51.31,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:51.79,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.84,0:03:54.27,Tsuritama_Main,BOSS,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:57.54,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:04:00.92,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.92,0:04:02.75,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,They don't believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.96,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,They would understand \Nif they had been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:09.85,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,The Bermuda Syndrome is \Nabout to strike again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:11.69,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Right here on Enoshima!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:16.56,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make dinner tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:20.55,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,That's great. You can use \Nthe rest of the whitebait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:22.78,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Maybe I'll make a salad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:24.24,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, be careful with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.24,0:04:25.87,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.70,0:04:37.56,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It feels great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:40.33,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Having your own pole's nice, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:41.49,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:42.63,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.37,0:04:44.96,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.96,0:04:46.27,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:48.68,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's going to play \Nsoccer instead of fish now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:50.51,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what he's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.61,0:04:53.98,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you can fool me with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.72,0:04:58.21,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Akira, why are you dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.21,0:05:00.16,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,It's supposed to rain today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:03.57,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:07.85,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've really \Ngotten into fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:09.71,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I've always liked fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:11.54,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you fish by yourself, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.34,0:05:16.35,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I have my reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.09,0:05:18.60,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:19.56,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:21.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you had fun the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:23.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Fishing for tuna with the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:28.58,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.58,0:05:30.56,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're not very cute, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:32.12,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,So, Natsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.12,0:05:34.30,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to teach me today?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:35.99,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not teaching you anything today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.99,0:05:36.75,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.75,0:05:40.18,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Fishing's something you \Nthink about for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:42.63,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Based on your current \Nlocation and conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.63,0:05:44.53,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you come up with your own strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.45,0:05:46.50,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,A strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.50,0:05:47.45,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:52.46,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,An angler's greatest moment \Nis when it all comes together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:53.56,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:55.13,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.49,0:05:57.92,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:06:01.43,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The sea bass are eating \NJapanese anchovies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.87,0:06:04.49,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Go for the sea bass out there today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.17,0:06:06.64,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.43,0:06:10.75,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's up to me? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.84,0:06:13.52,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,An angler has to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:16.09,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,a habit of always thinking \Nof how to fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.63,0:06:19.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,so you're always ready, no matter \Nwhat kind of tough catch appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:20.94,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,A tough catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.99,0:06:26.04,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I will go for the sea bass \Nwith this top water lure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.04,0:06:28.49,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. What about you, Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:29.57,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.57,0:06:31.82,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll think of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.90,0:06:39.64,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use this sinking lure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.64,0:06:40.79,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:42.06,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a hunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:44.42,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but I thought sea bass feeding at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:46.72,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,the surface must be small.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:49.62,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,I care more about numbers than size.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:06:52.51,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to catch a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:57.11,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling the big one's \Nbiding his time in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:06:59.91,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Is that the \Ncolor you want to use?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:00.89,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The color?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:03.35,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You should match the color of your lure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:05.67,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,to whatever the fish are eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:08.07,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.07,0:07:08.92,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This one, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:12.36,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Now you just have to figure \Nout how deep their prey is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.89,0:07:13.62,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:15.18,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,With a countdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:16.84,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,A countdown?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.84,0:07:19.59,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a method for measuring how long \Nit takes for your lure to sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.59,0:07:21.50,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But how am I supposed to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:23.32,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Figure it out yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.78,0:07:26.96,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,For example, this lure will sink \Nto the bottom in five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:34.18,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,One... two... three... four... five.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:39.64,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That means it'll be around \Nthe middle at three seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:42.95,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You can measure five levels \Nof depth this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:45.03,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:48.00,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you get a bite at three seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:49.74,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll know there are fish there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:53.52,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, the depth of the ocean \Nvaries from location to location.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:55.57,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,So I should cast over there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.57,0:07:57.57,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and measure the depth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:07:59.07,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:01.06,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:04.45,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Once I figure out where the fish are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.45,0:08:06.97,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bait the fish by making \Nthem think my lure's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:08.50,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:11.07,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:13.13,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,The first one to catch one wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.13,0:08:14.18,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.44,0:08:17.72,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Eno... shima... bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:36.62,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.19,0:08:38.93,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,He won't be easy to beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.93,0:08:41.95,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, why don't you \Nswitch to another lure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.90,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima bowl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:49.66,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But I decided I'd fish with this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:52.40,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,If you always use the same tactic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:54.05,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,your target will deceive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.41,0:08:57.89,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's not doing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:08:59.49,Tsuritama_Overlap,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.49,0:09:01.68,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's been testing all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:02.85,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.46,0:09:07.48,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:10.34,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for surprising you the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.34,0:09:13.06,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I won't do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.06,0:09:14.89,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.09,0:09:22.20,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,What terrible acting, Tapioca.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.18,0:09:24.20,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.91,0:09:27.25,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Onii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.25,0:09:28.75,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:30.23,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Catch anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:31.92,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:33.13,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:36.02,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll catch you a huge one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:38.52,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:41.35,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,The day after tomorrow's \Nmy brother's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:44.43,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:46.94,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.69,0:09:52.86,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to go fishing as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.38,0:09:56.16,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:09:59.61,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Aren't you going with your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.61,0:10:01.16,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be just my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.58,0:10:04.50,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Tapioca!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.97,0:10:10.21,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.21,0:10:12.94,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,This looks good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:14.92,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,I'll catch anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.31,0:10:17.30,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, come on, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:18.35,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Natsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.98,0:10:21.51,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, come on, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:30.23,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything okay now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.13,0:10:35.96,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,Did something sad happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.38,0:10:38.78,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:42.08,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,Your chest hurts, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.08,0:10:45.13,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Does your chest hurt sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.02,0:10:51.84,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, but you can't \Nfix it with a band-aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.84,0:10:53.38,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,How can I fix it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:55.14,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,You have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:10:56.70,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.13,0:10:58.34,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,You have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:03.01,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,Think really hard about what you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:04.90,Tsuritama_Main,KEITO,0000,0000,0000,,You have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.76,0:11:07.38,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Try...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:12.11,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:13.79,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.09,0:11:16.28,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,They're beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.54,0:11:19.31,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a present?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.31,0:11:20.43,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.43,0:11:22.24,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,This blue one's for my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:26.62,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,the purple one's for Dad,\Nmine's pink, and Mari-chan's is yellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.62,0:11:28.33,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,They're all our favorite colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.63,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make all of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.63,0:11:33.24,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.75,0:11:36.92,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,This string is Dad's fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.92,0:11:38.83,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:40.29,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What about this orange one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:41.66,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mom's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.15,0:11:44.30,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to put it on our family shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.30,0:11:45.46,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.46,0:11:47.76,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Natsuki will be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.76,0:11:51.62,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,But what will I do if he doesn't come?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:54.06,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura-chan, you're worried about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.42,0:11:57.86,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he really wants to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:02.10,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Let's all go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:04.99,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take my boat out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.42,0:12:06.68,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.68,0:12:07.62,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.62,0:12:11.26,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Weird things have been\Nhappening around here lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:13.81,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but we'll be fine as long \Nas we don't go out too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:15.63,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:18.71,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling things \Nwon't go so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.71,0:12:19.88,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:22.97,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,With everyone there, they cannot fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.97,0:12:26.10,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Indian, you say some \Nsmart things sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.38,0:12:29.07,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Haru-chan, you'll come, too, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:29.56,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:35.30,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to play ball in a cup that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:38.12,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,But... I want everyone to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:41.03,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,But my ball in a cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.03,0:12:43.67,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haru, enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:46.79,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You used to never shut up about fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.79,0:12:50.16,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,But it's dangerous in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:51.54,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.98,0:12:53.22,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The captain will be with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.22,0:12:54.41,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Haru.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.67,0:12:58.96,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone will be sad if you don't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:00.00,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.47,0:13:03.22,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:04.81,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:06.34,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Try?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.34,0:13:07.27,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.27,0:13:08.63,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:10.41,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it's better for \Neveryone to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:12.43,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:15.50,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow's our chance for \Neveryone to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.21,0:13:19.81,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to try to make Natsuki happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.55,0:13:24.38,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:27.07,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura, I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.49,0:13:30.81,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,It's better if everyone's \Nfriends, so I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:35.25,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Tapioca, this is our chance \Nto gather evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.02,0:13:54.11,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't get in our way tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.11,0:13:56.06,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like to be sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:14:01.21,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be friends \Nwith everyone forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.07,0:14:13.18,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Koko-chan, you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.18,0:14:14.76,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.76,0:14:16.21,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.21,0:14:18.96,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All right, everyone. All aboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:20.08,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:26.30,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.30,0:14:27.91,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:29.32,Tsuritama_Overlap,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,The loser will be punished!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:31.33,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.33,0:14:32.26,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:33.53,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.53,0:14:34.60,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Specialties!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:35.53,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Whitebait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.53,0:14:36.88,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Esca!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.03,0:14:40.95,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Mister Indian loses!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:42.31,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.35,0:14:46.29,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,One more time and you'll be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.29,0:14:47.40,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, alien.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:50.04,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Who knew you were so stupid, Indian?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:51.53,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Misaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:54.83,Tsuritama_Main,AKIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Enoshima!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.83,0:14:56.24,Tsuritama_Main,GIRL,0000,0000,0000,,Specialties!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.29,0:15:01.25,Tsuritama_Main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Punishment! Punishment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.07,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:29.03,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,When should I give these to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:30.64,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.64,0:15:32.32,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you when.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:35.03,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, Tamocchan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.03,0:15:36.52,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.49,0:15:39.04,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.69,0:15:40.82,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, Haru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.71,0:15:44.51,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Smile, Onii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:45.50,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.75,0:15:49.26,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,You're making a weird face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.64,0:15:53.49,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki, how is that a smile?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.49,0:15:54.84,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.84,0:15:55.78,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.78,0:15:57.65,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you're grumpy because you're the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:15:59.22,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,only one who hasn't caught anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:01.52,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed a bit \Nsince you were a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:07.84,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.\NNatsuki will catch something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:10.01,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They don't call him the \NFishing Prince for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.01,0:16:11.10,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.10,0:16:13.96,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,My son's gonna be a bass fishing pro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.48,0:16:17.58,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to my instruction, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.26,0:16:22.32,Tsuritama_Main,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:26.29,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never be a bass pro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:32.20,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You know I can't catch \Nblack bass on Enoshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.20,0:16:35.47,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't become a professional here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.66,0:16:39.33,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just take a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.33,0:16:40.47,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Then leave Enoshima!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.67,0:16:44.56,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:46.12,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:48.27,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you really want to \Nbe a pro, you'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:49.79,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What about the store?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.79,0:16:51.78,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.29,0:16:56.51,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking about converting \Nit into a whitebait carpet place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:17:00.11,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,We've all been coming up with \Nideas and getting ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.06,0:17:02.96,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,I have my own dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.96,0:17:04.23,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You have your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:06.71,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why wouldn't you tell me \Nsomething that important?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.71,0:17:09.40,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:11.42,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,That store is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.06,0:17:14.10,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to force \Nyourself to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.62,0:17:15.84,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You've got your own life to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:17.44,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But we're family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:19.43,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:25.80,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I really hate that about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:31.78,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on. No one likes \Nthis sort of atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:33.32,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we head back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.35,0:17:36.99,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out! A boat's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:39.16,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.54,Tsuritama_Main,KOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Nii-chan, is that him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.98,0:17:49.75,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.75,0:17:50.96,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Grab on, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:53.92,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let me down, Seishunmaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.75,0:17:57.47,Tsuritama_Main,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to port!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:07.17,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.56,0:18:09.69,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.22,0:18:19.38,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,Akira.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:20.88,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Haru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.63,0:18:23.08,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Sakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:24.85,Tsuritama_Main,HARU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.69,0:18:26.79,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.44,0:18:28.32,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:31.99,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped the orange one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.99,0:18:33.67,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom's favorite color.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:35.63,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault, Onii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:38.19,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.86,0:18:41.05,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to give you your present,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.81,0:18:43.88,Tsuritama_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but you had to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.88,0:18:47.31,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom... Mom's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.31,0:18:50.06,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I'll make you a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:53.08,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,No! I don't want you to make one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:56.49,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you get along with Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:59.13,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't you smile even\Nthough everyone's having fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:02.30,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Onii-chan, you're a jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.30,0:19:03.45,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.44,0:19:18.64,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,You're a jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:21.28,Tsuritama_Main,SAKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.60,0:19:23.64,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Do what you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.42,0:19:26.47,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.37,0:19:28.41,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:29.85,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.46,0:19:32.41,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize to Sakura-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.41,0:19:35.29,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura-chan worked really hard \Nto make those for everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.29,0:19:37.24,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What would you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:38.93,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.19,0:19:41.24,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.39,0:20:04.27,Tsuritama_Flashback,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,You've got your own life to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.27,0:20:05.64,Tsuritama_Flashback,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But we're family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:08.97,Tsuritama_Flashback,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What would you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:15.65,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That day, I fought with my \Nfriends for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.01,0:20:19.00,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.23,0:20:23.18,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.78,0:20:27.24,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about \Nparents or siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.47,0:20:29.16,Tsuritama_Main,TAMOTSU,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Sakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.01,0:20:31.84,Tsuritama_Main,NATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,She's not with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:39.72,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was so frustrated, \NI couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.03,0:20:50.37,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He... He... Hel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.37,0:20:52.06,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:53.14,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.14,0:20:56.15,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura-chan isn't with you, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.15,0:20:57.66,Tsuritama_Main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We can't find her anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.66,0:20:59.82,Tsuritama_Main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura-chan's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.13,0:21:03.49,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,a long, long night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:07.84,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,And I still didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:11.51,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,what was happening on Enoshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:15.11,Tsuritama_Italics/Thought,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
